          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A secondary beam of 11Be was produced from a primary",
                " beam of 13C bombarding on a 456 mg/cm2 Be target.",
                " Beam intensity and purity of 11Be were up to 10000",
                " particles per second (pps) and 95%, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A polythene (CH2)n target with thickness of 4.0+-0.05",
                " mg/cm2, while a 12.58+-0.10 mg/cm2 thick carbon",
                " target was employed to subtract the background from",
                " carbon atoms in the (CH2)n target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two parallel plate avalanche counters",
                " with a tracking efficiency of about 90% were",
                " installed upstream of a plastic scintillator, to",
                " provide energy loss and time-of-flight (TOF)",
                " information to identify the incoming particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The telescope TELE0, to detect 10Be",
                " from 11Be(p,d)10Be transfer reaction, comprised of a",
                " double-sided silicon strip detector (DSSD) with",
                " thickness of 1000 um and two large surface silicon",
                " detectors (SSDs) with thickness of 1500 um, was",
                " centered at the beam line with a distance of 200 mm",
                " away from the target and covered an angular scope of",
                " 0-10 deg in the laboratory frame."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SI",
                "CSICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The telescope TELE2, to detect",
                " d from 11Be(p,d)10Be transfer reaction, was placed",
                " 235 mm away from the target with central angle of 25",
                " deg relative to the beam line, composed of a",
                " 65-um-thick SSD, a 300-um-thick DSSD, a 1500-um-thick",
                " SSD and a layer of four CsI(Tl) crystals. Each",
                " crystal has an active area of 4.0x4.0 cm2 and a",
                " length of 4.1 cm.",
                "All the SSDs and DSSDs have an active area of",
                " 62.5x62.5 mm2. The width of each DSSD strip is 2 mm,",
                " bringing in an angular resolution of less than 0.6 deg",
                " for the detection of 10Be and deuterons. The energy",
                " resolution for all the silicon detectors was less",
                " than 1% for the 5.486 MeV alpha particle."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " To identify the incoming particles."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Beryllium isotopes from different reaction",
                " channels were identified based on a basic Delta E-E",
                " method."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The (p,d) transfer reaction was performed in",
                " inverse kinematics, in which the projectile-like",
                " fragments 10Be emitting at forward angles were",
                " measured in coincidence with the recoil deuterons."
              ]
            }
          ],
